# 957b7d9bbd614ec9bde590e7fdd620ad
#: ../source/read.rst:8
msgid ""
"The Read activity allows the laptop to act as a book reader. It has a simple "
"interface, and will view many kinds of text and image-based book-like "
"materials. It will have particular strengths in handheld mode, with "
"extremely low power consumption and simple navigation controls."
msgstr ""

# 63a53e868b764926bb27431bc995d9d3
#: ../source/read.rst:10
msgid ""
"Read can read PDF files, EPUB files, text files and single-page TIFF files."
msgstr ""

# fd67b1f4f027462588bfcb2fd3272a5c
#: ../source/read.rst:13
msgid "Using"
msgstr ""

# a2307de560ff4dbda7ddc018d2ad1dbc
#: ../source/read.rst:15
msgid ""
"The Read activity is launched by opening the Journal and choosing a PDF "
"document. PDFs downloaded from Browse can be opened in this way, as can PDFs "
"on an external storage device. The user may also start Read from the Home "
"page Favorites circle and select a file to read. The book opens in a "
"portrait orientation."
msgstr ""

# ff351883030340b2946503d1c77e712e
#: ../source/read.rst:21
msgid "Navigation"
msgstr ""

# 41cda56f498f4b1eb0fdbf744f457689
#: ../source/read.rst:23
msgid ""
"When the screen is in the upright position, the keyboard is available for "
"navigation as well as the directional pad and games keys. When the screen is "
"in tablet mode, the keyboard is not available. Make sure the document canvas "
"is selected (and not the tool-bar menu) by clicking either in the page area, "
"or pressing the TAB key until focus moves out of the toolbar."
msgstr ""

# 49ae728e17ef4df781fdcfff305c3431
#: ../source/read.rst:25
msgid "**Keyboard Navigation:**"
msgstr ""

# d4c04a18be704e8eb8056ae03e1c1e00
#: ../source/read.rst:27
msgid "The arrow keys will scroll the page a few lines in any direction"
msgstr ""

# 3910608f6da74109b0b03cf9633fd61b
#: ../source/read.rst:28
msgid ""
"ALT + arrow keys, or screen direction pad, will scroll the page a small "
"amount in any direction"
msgstr ""

# a5441c840b934c869927d93fa01eab4e
#: ../source/read.rst:29
msgid ""
"FN + arrow keys up/down will move one page up or down (with a small overlap "
"to keep context)"
msgstr ""

# f0d05fa3c3bd498c9253d27ad203439e
#: ../source/read.rst:30
msgid ""
"FN + arrow keys right/left will jump to the start or end of the document"
msgstr ""

# 8916a3ad1e5240e5b94e4d4c5088b9bf
#: ../source/read.rst:31
msgid "The keys h, j, k, l also act as left, down, up, right"
msgstr ""

# 8f8e7824bfc244298b55c241184b194a
#: ../source/read.rst:33
msgid "**Screen GamePad and Directional Button Navigation**"
msgstr ""

# 34d3460abf67465b885bb3ec906060d9
#: ../source/read.rst:35
msgid ""
"The screen rotation key (the bottom key on the left side of the screen) will "
"turn the screen image to accommodate tablet use."
msgstr ""

# 9c8323af065543e58586bad80f723448
#: ../source/read.rst:36
msgid ""
"The directional pad on the left hand side of the screen will also scroll a "
"few lines"
msgstr ""

# c1e061c93fad4d47b1535bd7399d9f4a
#: ../source/read.rst:37
msgid ""
"On the right hand side of the screen the gamepad buttons 'circle' and "
"'cross' also act as page up and page down (with a small overlap to keep "
"context)."
msgstr ""

# 41b48c3aa42148febee2c2b9bb399ad3
#: ../source/read.rst:38
msgid "The gamepad buttons 'square' and 'tick' act as a zoom in and zoom out"
msgstr ""

# f38f4e3c8b2641c1b31cd2b2994c0b28
#: ../source/read.rst:40
msgid "**Brightness Control**"
msgstr ""

# c9b564df012c49549ad795ee66029073
#: ../source/read.rst:42
msgid "The brightness can be increased or decreased with the keys"
msgstr ""

# e762148f93314993b9923295b5d2a2eb
#: ../source/read.rst:43
msgid ""
"Clarity is improved in tablet mode (turning the screen and laying it flat) "
"by using monochrome mode. Select CTRL + Brightness keys to turn it on or off."
msgstr ""

# 5bc5ebd0289c4141b446081a5befb29c
#: ../source/read.rst:44
msgid "Monochrome outside is easier to view books (CTRL Brightness Down)"
msgstr ""

# 9cbb6623c6f747688a7f0dcc6d966d22
#: ../source/read.rst:50
msgid "Be aware that large books may open and scroll slowly."
msgstr ""

# e9c97a966c71405e9916555475093c35
#: ../source/read.rst:53
msgid "Applying"
msgstr ""

# 15861923e18b4e7b96c74f190acc7e4b
#: ../source/read.rst:55
msgid ""
"The GetBooks Activity provides a way to expand access to many of the free "
"books available worldwide. The 'My Documents' folder appears at the bottom "
"of the screen when you are using Journal. Books can be stored in the My "
"Documents folder for easier cataloging."
msgstr ""
